import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].mean(), color='red', label='mean delay = {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].median(), color='green', label='median delay = {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['distance']]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data['distance'], vert=False, showmeans=True, meanline=True, labels=['Distance'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    ax.set_title('What is the average distance of flights?')
    ax.axvline(data['distance'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["distance"].mean():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = 1
    origin_counts = data.groupby('origin').count().sort_values(by='count', ascending=False).head(10)
    destination_counts = data.groupby('destination').count().sort_values(by='count', ascending=False).head(10)
    fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 6))
    ax1.bar(origin_counts.index, origin_counts['count'], color='blue')
    ax1.set_title('Top 10 Origin Airports')
    ax1.set_xlabel('Airport Code')
    ax1.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    ax1.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
    ax2.bar(destination_counts.index, destination_counts['count'], color='green')
    ax2.set_title('Top 10 Destination Airports')
    ax2.set_xlabel('Airport Code')
    ax2.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    ax2.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
    plt.suptitle('Which airports have the most flights?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['distance'], data['delay'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Delay (minutes)')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between distance and delay?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['hour'] = data['date'].dt.hour
    hour_counts = data.groupby('hour').size()
    plt.plot(hour_counts.index, hour_counts.values, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(hour_counts.idxmax(), color='red', label=f'Maximum: {hour_counts.max():.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Hour of Day')
    plt.ylabel('Flight Count')
    plt.title('What is the busiest time of day for flights?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
